🚨 Now the Revocation Problem

Imagine this situation:

User logs in → gets JWT valid for 1 hour.

After 5 minutes:

User logs out
OR

User account is banned
OR

Password is changed
OR

Token is stolen

But the token is still cryptographically valid.

Since services only check:

Signature

Expiry

The token continues working until it expires.

That is what:

"JWT cannot be easily revoked"

means.

There is no central place where you can say:

Invalidate this specific token immediately

Because no one is storing it.